Quarterly commentary  



Total returns details  






People and process

Firms
Vanguard Fixed Income Group
Product management
Vanguard Pennsylvania Long-Term Tax-Exempt Fund seeks high current income by investing at least 80% of its assets in municipal securities that are exempt from federal and Pennsylvania taxes. These municipal bonds are generally of long and intermediate maturity. The fund also may invest up to 20% in Pennsylvania alternative minimum tax bonds. The fund is conservatively managed, emphasizing well-diversified, highly-rated municipal bonds. Although the fund has no limitation on the maturity of individual securities, its dollar-weighted average nominal maturity is expected to be between 10 and 25 years.
